.TH "devm_drm_panel_bridge_add" 9 "devm_drm_panel_bridge_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_drm_panel_bridge_add \- Creates a managed &drm_bridge and &drm_connector that just calls the appropriate functions from &drm_panel.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct drm_bridge *" devm_drm_panel_bridge_add
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_panel *panel "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device to tie the bridge lifetime to
.IP "panel" 12
The drm_panel being wrapped.  Must be non-NULL.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is the managed version of \fBdrm_panel_bridge_add\fP which automatically
calls \fBdrm_panel_bridge_remove\fP when \fIdev\fP is unbound.
